&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hi, I&amp;rsquo;m Pippin. I make &lt;a href="https://pippinbarr.github.io/games/"&gt;games&lt;/a&gt;. I&amp;rsquo;m kind of on &lt;a href="https://bsky.app/profile/pippinbarr.bsky.social"&gt;Bluesky&lt;/a&gt;, and definitely on &lt;a href="mailto:pippin.barr@gmail.com"&gt;email&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m an Associate Professor in the &lt;a href="http://www.concordia.ca/finearts/design.html"&gt;Department of Design and Computation Arts&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href="http://www.concordia.ca/"&gt;Concordia University&lt;/a&gt; in Montréal. I&amp;rsquo;m also the department chair right now. I&amp;rsquo;m a member of the &lt;a href="http://tag.hexagram.ca/"&gt;Technoculture, Art, and Games (TAG) Research Centre&lt;/a&gt;, part of the &lt;a href="http://milieux.concordia.ca/"&gt;Milieux Institute for Arts, Culture, and Technology&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I teach or have taught creative programming, game design and development, game analysis and criticism, and internet/web-based art. Previously I have taught at the &lt;a href="http://www.um.edu.mt/about/academic/institutes"&gt;Institute of Digital Games&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href="http://www.um.edu.mt/"&gt;University of Malta&lt;/a&gt; (2012-2015), the &lt;a href="http://game.itu.dk/"&gt;Center for Computer Games Research&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href="http://www.itu.dk/"&gt;IT University of Copenhagen&lt;/a&gt; in Denmark (2009-2012), and the &lt;a href="http://hotsoft.carleton.ca/"&gt;HotSoft Lab&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href="http://carleton.ca/"&gt;Carleton University&lt;/a&gt; in Ottawa, Canada (2008-2009).&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Curriculum Vitae</title><link>https://pippinbarr.github.io/cv/</link><pubDate>Thu, 28 Apr 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pippinbarr.github.io/cv/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="pippin-barr-phd"&gt;Pippin Barr, PhD&lt;/h1&gt;
